==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bunch grass
<hw>Bunch" grass`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A grass
growing in bunches and affording pasture. In California, <spn>Atropis
tenuifolia</spn>, <spn>Festuca scabrella</spn>, and several kinds of
<spn>Stipa</spn> are favorite bunch grasses. In Utah, <spn>Eriocoma
cuspidata</spn> is a good bunch grass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bunchiness</ent>⟦br⟧
